, "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2019-09-13T18:03:09Z", "updated_at": "2019-09-13T18:03:09Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "#### What is the problem?\r\n\r\nOur run record ATM records the actual ran command, and not the actual original invocation of `datalad *run`: we place all the inputs outputs etc.  In the case of `datalad-containers-run` execution, we even add a prefix for invocation via container.\r\nAlthough it makes it possible to `rerun` exactly that command, it is ATM not so easy to \"re-execute\" that command with some modifications, e.g. adding, removing or changing some command option, or in the case of `datalad container` possibly switching to use another container.\r\n\r\nIt would be nice if we recorded the original invocation (e.g. `\"datalad containers-run -n containers/bids-mriqc  --input sourcedata --output . '{inputs}' '{outputs}' participant group\"`), i.e. exact command line if ran from the command line or Python invocation signature somewhere in the record (or sidecar).  This would allow easy \"human reexecution\" with possible modification of the command.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3673/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3673/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}